idDesc:
Since a cone is, in particular, a commutative diagram, and every functor
preserves commutativity of diagrams, a functor acts on a cone over (in
), sending it to a cone over (in ).

A category is called thin if all of its hom-sets are propositions rather
than sets. Furthermore, we require that the space of objects be a set;
In other words, a thin category is necessarily strict.
